OL,3,CFirst black female CoE deacon loses
OL,4,Cappeal over decision to dissolve parish
OL,6,FThe first black female deacon in the
OL,7,FChurch of England has lost an appeal
OL,8,Fover the decision to dissolve her
OL,9,Fparish.
OL,11,FReverend Yvonne Clarke was ordained as
OL,12,Fa deacon in the CoE in 1987 and has
OL,13,Fserved All Saints Shirley, in
OL,14,FSouthwark Diocese, for more than 20
OL,15,Fyears.
OL,17,FHowever, cost-cutting proposals by the
OL,18,FDiocese of Southwark, approved in
OL,19,FSeptember 2021, are set to dissolve
OL,20,Fher parish and divide it between two
OL,21,Fother parishes in south London.
