OL,3,CFirst black female CoE deacon loses
OL,4,Cappeal over decision to dissolve parish
OL,6,FGiving the committee's unanimous
OL,7,Fdecision, Lord Hodge said they were
OL,8,F"satisfied that the decision to make
OL,9,Fthe scheme did not involve unlawful
OL,10,Fdiscrimination or any failure to take
OL,11,Finto account the needs of minority
OL,12,Fethnic communities".
OL,14,FIn a 23-page ruling, he said the CoE's
OL,15,Fcommissioners were not acting as a
OL,16,Fpublic authority and also rejected an
OL,17,Fargument that the decision to dissolve
OL,18,Fthe parish was "indirectly
OL,19,Fdiscriminatory".
