OL,6,FLord Hodge ` sitting with Lords Sales,
OL,7,FHamblen, Leggatt and Richards ` also
OL,8,Fsaid they did not have the power to
OL,9,Fhear the appeal, and that the Judicial
OL,10,FCommittee of the Privy Council would
OL,11,Fonly intervene "in relatively limited
OL,12,Fcircumstances".
OL,14,FHe continued: "Such circumstances
OL,15,Finclude where there has been a
OL,16,Fsignificant procedural irregularity or
OL,17,Fexcess of jurisdiction, where there
OL,18,Fhas been an error in principle in the
OL,19,Fdecision or otherwise the decision-
OL,20,Fmaker has clearly gone wrong."
